author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: - take time getting used to without them. I know I won't heal that quickly, but at least I'm trying my best. So please, don't tell someone to "just get over it" if they seem down in the dumps all the time. It could make things a lost worse.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: I've been in therapy for many, many years. Even now I'm still having sessions. Ever since the passing of two of my most precious family members, I've been trying more and more to get back in the swing of things. But there's certain times of the year (like Christmas) that still -

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: That was basically it. I just lost all sense of being and I broke down sobbing on the floor, screaming and crying. I stayed home from work for about a week. I barely got out of bed. I couldn't sleep. My depression was so high I just didn't care about anything anymore.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: We both loved each other very much. But Jared also had problems with epilepsy. And one night two summers ago it cost him his life. His older brother texted me on Facebook the next day and told me Jared had passed away in his sleep overnight.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: I visited him several times in the summer and we instantly grew very close to each other. This was the first time in my life I could actually be my true self around another person. Someone who didn't care what I looked or acted like.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: About a year later I lost another important person to me: my boyfriend, Jared, who lived long distance in the state of Washington (originally from Oregon). I knew him from online gaming and we talked on and off for about ten years.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: So when my grandma heard what was going on she put her foot down and invited me to live with her and her husband. And I've been living here since she passed away two years ago. She had stage 4 pancreatic cancer and it wrecked her all over.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: She always got into fights and often times stayed at someone else's place for several days without telling me where she was. I couldn't even buy myself food because I couldn't get a job. And we were about to be evicted because bills weren't being paid.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: My grandma was the only person in my family who actually helped me when I needed it. She pulled me out of a shitty house and let me stay in her home where I still live to this day. My mom was an alcoholic and would always come home wasted.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text: And I hate when my step granddad or any of his relatives have the absolute gall to tell me to "get over it" and to just be happy again. Hearing these types of attitudes just makes me feel even worse and doesn't do jack shit to help me.

author: Heisenberg is a greasy himbo
text:
TW: depressing, angsty, a bit salty

I used to love the Holidays. Yes, that's right, /used to/. Losing two people who were super close to me really took a toll on my mental health to the point where I just can't find it in myself to enjoy things anymore.
